  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Raising Income of Condition Cash Transfer (CCT) Families through Sustainable Agri-Business (RICSA)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, Heifer Philippines will focus on values-based cooperative development, improved animal management, and business development. Interventions will be reinforced through sustainable agroecological management practices like biogas digesters, vermicomposting and proper animal housing that also prevent water contamination. Heifer and its partners will assist families with technical and financial support services that will strengthen communities and promote leadership, especially among women. Additionally, the project will integrate Disaster Risk Reduction Management (DRRM) and climate change adaptation plans and activities to ensure communities can endure and quickly recover from disaster events.</narrative>
  </description>
